    "This indicates the robustness and transferability of our model's attribution capability when trained with fine-grained rewards.Trained LLMs have high factual precision.",
    "While we do not use factuality as a reward model, the FActscore (Min et al., 2023) metric shows that more than 80% of sentences generated by our methods are factual, which is close to that of ChatGPT.",
    "Related WorkRetrieval-Augmented Language Models (RALM).",
    "There exists prior work on RALMs for tasks such as question-answering and factchecking.",
    "Aside from the works on kNN-LM (Khandelwal et al., 2020; Zhong et al., 2022), most of them involve (1) document selection and (2) document reading."
